review_blob: 50cl bottle. Amber beer with a litttle foam,  caramel, nuts,  light sweetness. A short finish.
50cl bottle. Amber color beer with no head and totally flat, look like a tea with some taste of hops, and nothing else. Mistake i think.
50cl bottle. Pours hazy yellow with white head. Aroma its not good, acidic. Astringent, acid and citric. To fix!
50cl bottle at bir&fud; beershop. A golden in apparence, with a very little aroma of caramel, lightly bitter, light body, lively carbonation. I dont like this beer, too poor.

33cl & 75cl Bottle from bir&fud; beershop. 
Amber italian IPA with a good white foam. Complex nose with alla merican hops:  caramel, resin, floral, citrus, grapefruit, fantastic. A medium body, with medium carbonation. Palate with a great grapefruit, orange,  citrus and fresh fruit with a bitter long finish.

75cl Bottle from bir&fud; beershop. 
Every year Birra del Borgo change his recept for this fantastic IPA, starting from the basic ReAle. This 5 anniversay with nelson sauvin its an orange, hazy, ipa with a good white foam. Aroma: floral, resin, citrus, grapefruit, passion fruit a complete bouquet!!!
A good bitterness on mouth balanced with medium body, and soft carbonation. A long bitter finish for this great anniversary reale.

Rare & Famous beer from the monk of St. Sixtus!
33cl Bottle at the monk bar in front of the abbey. A dark brown strong ale/quad with a good head, served in the right glass! Aroma is a full of tofee, caramel, cookie, a bit of chocolate. Medium sweetness, full body, creamy, with toffee again on palate and red fruit, chocolate caramel. A full full body beer :D very long final! To try before die.

330 ml bottle.
What a beer! I think the best trappist with Westy 8. Dark brown colour with a nice head. Aroma/Palate: at first caramel, after dark/reds fruits, and hints of chocolate. Wonderful! Medium sweetness, full body, creamy, soft carbonation.

Darkness black with a very dark brown head, like Cappuccino :D. Aroma is coffee, bitter chocolate and hops! Very heavy body, its like eat bread! Palate chocolate again, coffe, bread, toast, roasty a wonderful Imperial Stout from usa!
Good creamy head but too much alcohol on the nose and palate, not my beer. Not balanced...

Wow the first brew from Turan and what a brew! An imperial Stout at 7,2%, chocolate and coffee at first on the nose and then a balanced roasty. 
Palate: the nose is respected on palate! Great balance. Bit hoppy. Chocholate/coffe/roasty. Interesting and complex. First great Job.
